The Padawan municipality is a collective name given to a subset of the Kuching District area which is not administered locally by the Kuching South City Council and the Kuching North City Hall, formerly known as Kuching Rural district. It has an area of 1771.3  km2, covering the suburbs of the Kuching Proper subdistrict and Padawan subdistrict. The area is currently administered by state-based internal  government, Padawan Municipal Council. Kota Padawan exists 16 kilometres south from the centre of Kuching. The centre of Padawan is Batu 10 with it being the seat of the Padawan Municipal Council.

